    "prerequisites": ["time-matrix-15"],
    "lesson_content_markdown": "# Cause of the Past: Past Perfect Continuous\n\nSometimes, we want to explain **why** something was true in the past. If the cause was an action that had a duration, we use the **Past Perfect Continuous**.\n\n### 1. The Timeline\nImagine your roommate was very tired yesterday.\n- **The State (Past)**: My roommate was tired.\n- **The Cause (Earlier Action)**: He was studying for 5 hours.\n- **Combined**: *\"My roommate was tired because he **had been studying** for five hours.\"*\n\n### 2. How to Make It\nUse **had** + **been** + **V-ing**.\n\n- **Formula**: Subject + had + been + doing word (ing)\n- **Example**: The laboratory floor was wet because the technician **had been cleaning** it.\n\n### 3. Difference: Past Perfect vs. Past Perfect Continuous\n- **Past Perfect**: He was happy because he **had finished** the test. (The result of a completed action.)\n- **Past Perfect Continuous**: He was tired because he **had been working** out. (The focus is on the action happening for a long time.)\n\n---",
